  "text": " More and more people are beginning to see credit as key to realizing their dreams. Lenders must find ways of making credit accessible to more customers at a fraction of the time while minimizing risks. Banks are continuously engaged in evolving policies to tackle ever-rising credit supply demand mismatches. How do we make policies solve this demand supply problem? Does data analytics hold the key? Let's work towards it. The easy to configure Brex helps in an easy configurability and making the policy active within minutes. Let's look at how a typical policy framing takes into consideration various parameters to arrive at a lending decision. The policy selection takes into account key identifiers such as product, source system, priority, validity status or custom criteria. Then it decides which policy outcome to display. Scorecards is one such crucial outcome that is generated along with other supporting outcomes such as derived fields decision rules and eligibility calculations etc The platform takes data from different categories such as application data or any other third party integration like bureau, bank statement analyzers, etc. Each category has multiple attributes associated with it. 70 is the average number of attributes though it varies for each product. Attributes are scored based on different variables present on the platform. These variables are either custom computed or derived variables or they can also be raw variables. Conditions are applied on these variables and divided into different scoring ranges. Then applying correct weightage to score from these range, the final score of the attribute is calculated. This platform gives access to pre and tested scorecards which can further be customized easily as required by the products Once the policy is active and any customer walks in for a loan the bank lending platform which is equipped with Lentra automated scorecards and Brex takes over for automated decisioning As part of the application, the customer's identifiers are keyed into the digital interface. interface. The input triggers a well-orchestrated and microservice-based architecture of Lentra's OpenAPI stack. This orchestration allows the platform to collect information from bureaus, negative lists, social media, etc. and runs them within the powerful Brex decisioning engine, thereby invoking necessary credit policies and rules. Brex invokes the policy based on the application type and initiates an internal API called the scorecards. Scorecards are created by pulling all data available from bureau, bank statement, financial statement ITR GST device and social media into relevant variables using AINLP in LP based algorithms fast variables are fed into MLB decisioning models and case based way to just to arrive at a comprehensive score the output of this is matched against the scorecards indicator index giving a very clear understanding of the customer profile and an immediate decisioning Brex evaluates the score for approval or rejection against pre-built logic for risk assessment and creditworthiness. The customer sees the approved loan amount along with all other terms and conditions like applicable rate of interest, payback terms and schedules, and an option to proceed with disbursement. Witness your lending business grow while boosting application approvals and loan dispersals. Brex. Data streams to automated decisions, instantly. you",
